## 9. ACTIVE VOICE AND RESPONSIBILITY

### Kogan et al. (strong examples)

> "We propose a new measure..."
> "We construct this measure combining..."
> "We find that our measure is associated with..."

**Not:**
> "A new measure is proposed..."
> "It is found that the measure is associated with..."

### MRW

> "This paper takes Robert Solow seriously."
> "We show that..."

**Principle:** Take responsibility. Use "I" or "We" for claims and methods.

